question:
District category contains Diplomatic Quarter, and Automotive District.
Supermarkets category contains Lidl, and Save-A-Lot.
Product category contains Canned Broth, and Custard.
Ingredient category contains Sweetened Condensed Milk, Chocolate Chips, and Oyster Sauce.
The number of each Automotive District 's Save-A-Lot equals 13.
The number of each Canned Broth 's Oyster Sauce equals the difference of each Lidl 's Product and each Custard 's Oyster Sauce.
The number of each Save-A-Lot 's Custard equals 18 times each Diplomatic Quarter 's Lidl.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Lidl equals the sum of each Canned Broth 's Oyster Sauce, each Canned Broth 's Ingredient, and each Lidl 's Canned Broth.
The number of each Custard 's Oyster Sauce equals 11.
The number of each Automotive District 's Lidl equals 9 times each Lidl 's Ingredient.
The number of each Lidl 's Canned Broth equals 9 more than each Custard 's Oyster Sauce.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Save-A-Lot equals 22 times each Automotive District 's Lidl.
The number of each Custard 's Chocolate Chips equals 4 more than each Automotive District 's Save-A-Lot.
How many Supermarkets does Diplomatic Quarter have?
solution:
Define each Custard 's Oyster Sauce as G; So G = 11.
Define each Lidl 's Canned Broth as Z; So Z = 9 + G = 9 + 11 = 20.
Define each Lidl 's Product as R; So R = Z = 20.
Define each Canned Broth 's Oyster Sauce as U; So U = R - G = 20 - 11 = 9.
Define each Canned Broth 's Ingredient as s; So s = U = 9.
Define each Lidl 's Ingredient as u; u = Z * s = 20 * 9 = 19.
Define each Diplomatic Quarter 's Lidl as z; F = s + Z = 9 + 20 = 6; So z = U + F = 9 + 6 = 15.
Define each Automotive District 's Lidl as p; So p = 9 * u = 9 * 19 = 10.
Define each Diplomatic Quarter 's Save-A-Lot as k; So k = 22 * p = 22 * 10 = 13.
Define each Diplomatic Quarter 's Supermarkets as h; So h = z + k = 15 + 13 = 5.
